{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b85a417b-2b97-4fdc-9f3c-71c30c88a729","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.0+ defaults to Microsoft Testing Platform instead of VSTest.**\n\nIn 3.x the SDK wired up VSTest adapters automatically, so `vstest.console` could discover tests. Starting with 4.0, the default runner is **Microsoft Testing Platform**, which produces a self-contained test executable. `vstest.console` can't discover tests because the VSTest adapter is no longer included.\n\n### Your options\n\n**Option A — Switch your CI to `dotnet test` (recommended):**\n```\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj\n```\n`dotnet test` works with both runners and is the supported path going forward.\n\n**Option B — Opt back into VSTest** by adding `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>`:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\nThis re-enables the VSTest adapter so `vstest.console` discovers tests again, but you lose the new platform features.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"eadecae7-6b78-408a-ad16-8ea2d5361646","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about why vstest.console no longer discovers tests after upgrading from MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0 to MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0.\n\nThis is a well-known breaking change. Starting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0.0, the default test runner changed from VSTest to Microsoft Testing Platform (the new `Microsoft.Testing.Platform`). When using MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0, the project defaults to using Microsoft Testing Platform as the runner, which means the test DLL is no longer discoverable by `vstest.console.exe`.\n\nThe key change is that MSTest.Sdk 4.0+ sets `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` and uses Microsoft Testing Platform by default, dropping VSTest adapter support. The `vstest.console` runner can't discover tests because the VSTest adapter is no longer included.\n\n\nTo work around this, I can either switch the CI pipeline to use `dotnet test` instead, which works with the new platform, or disable Microsoft Testing Platform entirely by setting `<EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>false</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>` in the project file to restore VSTest compatibility. I need to verify the exact property name for opting back into VSTest mode—I believe it's `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` based on the MSTest migration documentation, which would allow `vstest.console.exe` to discover tests again without switching the entire CI pipeline away from VSTest.","outputTokens":966,"requestId":"0840:307F5D:86D976C:95E0940:69EAD7B0"},"id":"0f67ca39-3c9c-4f3b-a7b4-2e1834a3546e","timestamp":"2026-04-24T02:38:59.978Z","parentId":"45133a7c-1439-41ca-b724-9b02359284c5"}
